																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">18</div> <div class="vers-content">But some man will say: Thou hast faith, and I have works: shew me thy faith without works; and I will shew thee, by works, my faith.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">18</div> <div class="vers-content">We shall be inclined to say to him, Thou hast faith, but I have deeds to shew. Shew me this faith of thine without any deeds to prove it, and I am prepared, by my deeds, to prove my own faith. </div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">19</div> <div class="vers-content">Tu credis quoniam unus est Deus: bene facis: et dÃ¦mones credunt, et contremiscunt.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">19</div> <div class="vers-content">Thou believest that there is one God. Thou dost well: the devils also believe and tremble.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">19</div> <div class="vers-content">Thou believest that there is only one God; that is well enough, but then, so do the devils, and the devils shrink from him in terror.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">20</div> <div class="vers-content">Vis autem scire, o homo inanis, quoniam fides sine operibus mortua est?</div></div></td>
